<br>
Gun nazis always crack me up.  The officer here used his sidearm to stop someone trying to run him over.  I saw no mention of the guy in the car having a gun.  If this was in England or some other bastion of socialism, the officer would likely have been run over while trying to billy club or scold the driver or whatever peace officers are allowed to do there.  This whole incident shows why arming police officers is not a product of having an armed populace.<br>
<br>
If the driver had been drunk and run over a day care center, people would be ready to hang him by the testicles in the town square.  Yet because he made the same bad choices that a drunk driver makes when getting behind the wheel,  placing the public at risk with his actions, and dies because of it, now he is suddenly a victim?  Sorry, doesn't work for me.<br>
